        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/wW1C6.png?s=256",
        "display_name" : "A.H.",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/947357/a-h"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 8,
      "creation_date" : 1317771345,
      "post_id" : 7655177,
      "comment_id" : 9301068,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Both methods call <code>String(char[])</code> or a variant of that. And the copy part is done inside <code>String(char[])</code>. This leaves no benefit to a direct call besides symmetry with the other <code>valueOf</code> methods."
